  "doc_id": "3202",
  "text": "We have implemented the IB-PRE part of our system by modifying the Green-Ateniese IBE-PRE implementation included in the Charm Crypto library [CITATION_1] to support RSA public keys for the delegatee. In order to achieve a security level equivalent to RSA with a key size of 1024 bits for the encryption of the symmetric key, the size of C ID (key) is 3232 bits, and the size of a re-encryption key is 1536 bits. In an Ubuntu 12.04 Desktop machine, running in a single core of an Intel i5-4440 3.1 GHz processor with 2GB of RAM, the creation of C ID (key) required 40 ms, the creation of a reencryption key required 20 ms, the re-encryption of a ciphertext required 31 ms, and the decryption of a ciphertext required 28 ms.",
